  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Following the original idea of Debye, we define and extract a gauge-invariant screening mass from the complex static in-medium heavy-quark potential <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">¯</mo></mrow></mover></mrow></msub></math> , recently obtained from lattice QCD. To this end we derive a formula using concepts from both effective- and classical field theories that faithfully reproduces both the screened real- and the imaginary part of the lattice potential with a single temperature dependent fit parameter <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>T</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> . Using values of the real part of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mover accent="true"><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mo stretchy="false">¯</mo></mrow></mover></mrow></msub></math> in a gluonic medium, we obtain Debye masses compatible with HTL perturbation theory.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
